comfortable there
and there weren't going to be
issues.

09:03.309 --> 09:07.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what happened was is that,
over that period
of time, they learned about a
deal Mr. O'Reilly

09:07.813 --> 09:09.715 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
had cut with a woman in 2011.

09:09.749 --> 09:12.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They allowed Mr. O'Reilly to cut
two more
deals.

09:12.585 --> 09:14.520 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then this was exposed, and it
put pressure
on them.

09:14.554 --> 09:17.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There were protests outside of
the network.

09:17.290 --> 09:22.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was a plane that flew a
banner around
New York City calling for Mr.
O'Reilly's ouster,

09:22.528 --> 09:24.730 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and there was real public
pressure on them.

09:24.764 --> 09:26.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think the sons really won
out here.

09:26.966 --> 09:31.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rupert has extreme loyalty to
Mr. O'Reilly,
who was one of the founding
hosts will of

09:31.103 --> 09:33.072 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the network when it started 20
years ago.

09:33.105 --> 09:37.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Michael Schmidt,
as somebody
who has covered network news,
covered related

09:38.010 --> 09:41.047 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stories, is this an earthquake
in television
news?

09:41.080 --> 09:46.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL SCHMIDT: Well, I think
Mr. O'Reilly's
probably the most recognized
host in cable

09:46.152 --> 09:47.119 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
television.

09:47.153 --> 09:48.454 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
